---
// The project's primary demoable artifact: upload a real fitness-app export, watch it get
// parsed into portable OpenBody JSON, entirely client-side. No file ever leaves the browser.
//
// This is a custom Astro page (outside the `docs` content collection) rather than an .mdx
// page, because it needs real interactivity (file upload, in-browser parsing, a client-side
// download) — Starlight's content collection is markdown/static. `StarlightPage` gives it the
// same header/sidebar/theme chrome as the rest of the site while letting the body be
// hand-written HTML + a vanilla client-side `<script>` (no UI framework needed or installed).
//
// Parsing uses the real @openbody/openbody-ts package directly (mapHevy, mapStrong,
// mapAppleHealth, mapStrava) — no vendored copy needed: openbody-ts's validate.ts no
// longer pulls in node:fs/path/url at module load, so the package is safe to import from
// browser-bundled code. Source detection + the thin activities.csv → mapStrava adapter
// live in src/components/convert-sources.ts.
import StarlightPage from "@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro";
import { Aside } from "@astrojs/starlight/components";
---

<StarlightPage
  frontmatter={{
    title: "Convert your workout data",
    description:
      "Upload a Hevy, Strong, Apple Health, or Strava export and see it parsed into portable OpenBody JSON, entirely in your browser. No signup, no server, no upload.",
    tableOfContents: false,
  }}
>
  <p><span class="ob-status">EXPERIMENTAL · pre-v1.0 tool</span></p>

  <p class="ob-lede">
    Your workout history is stuck in whatever app you logged it in. This is a small demo of
    what OpenBody is for: pick a real export from a fitness app, watch it parsed into a
    portable, human-readable record in your own browser, and download the result. Nothing is
    uploaded anywhere — the parsing code runs on your machine, not a server.
  </p>

  <Aside type="caution" title="Early, experimental">
    OpenBody itself is a <strong>pre-v1.0 draft standard</strong> (see the
    <a href="/specification/">specification</a>), and this converter is a demo tool, not a
    finished product. It reads the export formats below via the reference mappers in
    <a href="https://github.com/openbody/openbody-ts">openbody-ts</a>; each card says
    exactly what is and isn't read. More formats (FIT files, per-activity GPX) are planned;
    see the <a href="/mapping/">mapping guides</a> for the mappings that exist in the
    reference implementation.
  </Aside>

  <h2>Supported exports</h2>
  <div class="ob-source-grid">
    <div class="ob-source-card">
      <p class="ob-source-name">Hevy — workout CSV</p>
      <p class="ob-source-how">Hevy app → Profile → Settings → Export Data.</p>
      <p class="ob-source-what">
        Full lifting history: workouts, exercises, sets, reps, load, RPE, supersets.
        Exercise names are matched to canonical OpenBody movements where known.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="ob-source-card">
      <p class="ob-source-name">Hevy — body-measurement CSV</p>
      <p class="ob-source-how">Hevy app → Profile → Settings → Export Data (the
        <code>measurement_data.csv</code> alongside the workout export).</p>
      <p class="ob-source-what">
        Body metrics logged over time: weight and body-fat become canonical OpenBody
        measurements, and body circumferences (neck, chest, biceps, waist, …) map to the
        canonical anthropometry types — with the tape-measure unit (inches or centimetres)
        preserved from your Hevy setting.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="ob-source-card">
      <p class="ob-source-name">Strong — workout CSV</p>
      <p class="ob-source-how">Strong app → Profile → Settings → Export Strong Data.</p>
      <p class="ob-source-what">
        Workouts, exercises, sets, weight, reps, plus distance/time sets. Same canonical
        exercise matching as Hevy.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="ob-source-card">
      <p class="ob-source-name">Apple Health — export.xml</p>
      <p class="ob-source-how">
        Health app → profile picture → Export All Health Data, then <strong>unzip</strong>
        the export.zip and pick <code>export.xml</code>.
      </p>
      <p class="ob-source-what">
        Workouts become sessions (duration, distance, energy); heart rate, step count, body
        mass, and sleep-stage records become measurements. Per-workout GPS routes and other
        record types aren't read yet. Big exports can take a moment — it all runs locally.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="ob-source-card">
      <p class="ob-source-name">Strava — activities.csv</p>
      <p class="ob-source-how">
        strava.com → Settings → My Account → Download or Delete Your Account → Download
        Request, then pick <code>activities.csv</code> from the archive.
      </p>
      <p class="ob-source-what">
        Summary per activity only: sport, date, moving/elapsed time, distance. The GPS,
        heart-rate, and power streams (the GPX/FIT files in the same archive) are coming
        later.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Export your data from one of the apps above.</li>
    <li>Drop the file below — the format is detected automatically. Parsing happens entirely
      in your browser via JavaScript — the file is never sent anywhere.</li>
    <li>Review the summary and human-readable preview, then download the portable OpenBody
      JSON — and, for lifting exports, a Strong-format CSV that both Strong and Hevy can
      import.</li>
  </ol>

  <div id="convert-tool" class="ob-tool">
    <label id="drop-zone" for="file-input" class="ob-dropzone">
      <input
        id="file-input"
        type="file"
        multiple
        accept=".csv,.xml,.json,text/csv,text/xml,application/xml,application/json"
      />
      <span class="ob-dropzone-title">Choose one or more export files, or drag them here</span>
      <span class="ob-dropzone-sub">Hevy workout CSV · Hevy measurement CSV · Strong CSV · Apple Health export.xml · Strava activities.csv · an OpenBody JSON you exported earlier</span>
      <span class="ob-dropzone-sub">Add files from several apps and they merge into one history. Nothing is uploaded — it all runs in your browser.</span>
    </label>

    <div class="ob-option-row">
      <label for="subject-input">Subject ID (optional)</label>
      <input
        id="subject-input"
        type="text"
        placeholder="e.g. me, athlete-42"
        autocomplete="off"
        spellcheck="false"
      />
      <span class="ob-option-hint">
        The id every record is tagged with — applied to <em>every</em> file you add, so records
        from different apps share one subject and can be de-duplicated across sources. Leave blank
        and a placeholder (<code>subj-001</code>) is used instead.
      </span>
    </div>

    <p id="status" class="ob-status-msg" role="status" aria-live="polite" hidden></p>

    <p id="subject-note" class="ob-note" role="note" hidden></p>

    <div id="layers" class="ob-layers" hidden></div>

    <div id="summary" class="ob-summary" hidden></div>

    <div id="resolution" class="ob-resolution" hidden></div>

    <div id="preview" class="ob-preview" hidden></div>

    <div class="ob-downloads">
      <button id="download-btn" type="button" class="ob-btn ob-btn-primary" hidden>
        Download as OpenBody JSON
      </button>
      <button id="download-strong-btn" type="button" class="ob-btn ob-btn-secondary" hidden>
        Download as Strong CSV
      </button>
    </div>

    <div id="strong-info" class="ob-strong-info" hidden></div>

    <div id="email-capture" class="ob-email-card" hidden>
      <form id="email-form">
        <p class="ob-email-title">Want to know when more apps are supported?</p>
        <p class="ob-email-sub">
          Optional — totally skippable. We'll only email about new source formats for this
          tool and major OpenBody milestones.
        </p>
        <div class="ob-email-row">
          <input
            id="email-input"
            type="email"
            name="email"
            placeholder="you@example.com"
            required
            aria-label="Email address"
          />
          <button type="submit" class="ob-btn ob-btn-secondary">Notify me</button>
          <button id="email-dismiss" type="button" class="ob-btn ob-btn-ghost">No thanks</button>
        </div>
        <p id="email-status" class="ob-email-status" role="status" aria-live="polite"></p>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>What is "OpenBody JSON"?</h2>
  <p>
    The downloaded file is an array of OpenBody records — <code>Session</code> records for
    workouts, plus <code>Measurement</code> records for Apple Health data like heart rate
    and sleep stages. It's the same wire format documented in the
    <a href="/mapping/">mapping guides</a> and validated against the
    <a href="/specification/schema/">JSON Schema</a>: a plain, inspectable JSON file you
    own. Move it between tools, check it into your own backup, or feed it to anything else
    that speaks OpenBody.
  </p>

  <script>
    import "../../scripts/convert-tool";
  </script>

  {/* is:global (with page-unique ob- prefixes) because most of this UI is created by the
      client script at runtime: Astro's default scoping only tags elements that exist in
      the template, so scoped selectors never match JS-rendered nodes. */}
  <style is:global>
    .ob-lede {
      font-size: var(--sl-text-lg);
      max-width: 60ch;
    }

    .ob-tool {
      margin: 2rem 0;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .ob-source-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(17rem, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .ob-source-card {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-source-name {
      margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ob-source-how {
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }
    .ob-source-what {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }

    .ob-dropzone {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 0.35rem;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem;
      border: 2px dashed var(--sl-color-gray-5);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: border-color 0.15s ease, background-color 0.15s ease;
    }
    .ob-dropzone:hover,
    .ob-dropzone.is-dragover {
      border-color: var(--sl-color-accent);
      background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-accent) 6%, transparent);
    }
    .ob-dropzone input[type="file"] {
      position: absolute;
      width: 1px;
      height: 1px;
      opacity: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .ob-dropzone-title {
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ob-dropzone-sub {
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }

    /* Optional subject-id control — matches the email-capture input styling. */
    .ob-option-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: auto minmax(12rem, 22rem);
      grid-template-areas: "label input" "hint hint";
      gap: 0.35rem 0.75rem;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .ob-option-row label {
      grid-area: label;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
    }
    .ob-option-row input[type="text"] {
      grid-area: input;
      font: inherit;
      padding: 0.5rem 0.7rem;
      border-radius: 0.4rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg);
      color: var(--sl-color-text);
    }
    .ob-option-hint {
      grid-area: hint;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }
    @media (max-width: 34rem) {
      .ob-option-row {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        grid-template-areas: "label" "input" "hint";
        align-items: start;
      }
    }

    /* Neutral, informational note — deliberately NOT the warning/error style. Used for
       working-as-intended notices such as the placeholder-subject fallback. */
    .ob-note {
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
      padding: 0.6rem 0.9rem;
      border-radius: 0.35rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-note code {
      font-size: 0.95em;
    }

    /* Phase B: accumulated source layers with per-layer toggle + remove. */
    .ob-layers {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 0.9rem 1.1rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-layers-head {
      margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-layer-list {
      list-style: none;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .ob-layer {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
      padding: 0.5rem 0.65rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.4rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg);
    }
    .ob-layer-toggle {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.6rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      min-width: 0;
    }
    .ob-layer-toggle input[type="checkbox"] {
      flex: none;
      width: 1.05rem;
      height: 1.05rem;
      accent-color: var(--sl-color-accent);
      cursor: pointer;
    }
    .ob-layer-label {
      font-weight: 600;
      overflow-wrap: anywhere;
    }
    .ob-layer-count {
      flex: none;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      padding: 0.1rem 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
    }
    .ob-layer-remove {
      grid-column: 2;
      font: inherit;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      font-weight: 600;
      padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
      border-radius: 0.35rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
      background-color: transparent;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
      cursor: pointer;
    }
    .ob-layer-remove:hover {
      border-color: #b3261e;
      color: #b3261e;
    }
    .ob-layer-note {
      grid-column: 1 / -1;
      margin: 0.1rem 0 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }

    /* Merge headline (the payoff line) + per-kind dashboard panels. */
    .ob-merge-stats {
      margin: 0;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-lg);
      color: var(--sl-color-text);
    }
    .ob-panel {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    .ob-panel-title {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-base);
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--sl-color-white);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .ob-panel-body {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }

    .ob-status-msg {
      font-family: var(--sl-font-mono);
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      padding: 0.6rem 0.9rem;
      border-radius: 0.35rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
    }
    .ob-status-msg.is-info {
      border-color: var(--sl-color-gray-4);
    }
    .ob-status-msg.is-success {
      border-color: var(--sl-color-accent);
      color: var(--sl-color-text-accent);
      background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-accent) 8%, transparent);
    }
    .ob-status-msg.is-error {
      border-color: #b3261e;
      color: #b3261e;
    }

    .ob-resolution {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-resolution-title {
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ob-resolution-list {
      margin: 0;
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-resolution-name {
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ob-resolution-kept {
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }

    /* Unified post-conversion summary card. */
    .ob-summary {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-summary-title {
      margin: 0;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-lg);
    }
    .ob-chips {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      margin-top: 0.6rem;
    }
    .ob-chip {
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      font-weight: 600;
      padding: 0.15rem 0.6rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-accent) 35%, transparent);
      background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-accent) 8%, transparent);
      color: var(--sl-color-text);
    }
    .ob-summary-facts {
      margin: 0.6rem 0 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-summary-subhead {
      margin: 1rem 0 0.3rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }
    .ob-movements {
      margin: 0;
      padding-left: 1.4rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-movements li {
      margin: 0.1rem 0;
    }

    /* Weekly-activity sparkline: single accent, hairline baseline, no axes. */
    .ob-spark-wrap {
      max-width: 45rem;
    }
    .ob-spark {
      display: block;
      max-width: 100%;
    }
    .ob-spark rect {
      fill: var(--sl-color-accent);
    }
    .ob-spark-baseline {
      stroke: var(--sl-color-hairline);
      stroke-width: 1;
    }
    .ob-spark-labels {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      margin-top: 0.15rem;
    }

    .ob-downloads {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    .ob-downloads:not(:has(button:not([hidden]))) {
      display: none;
    }

    /* Strong-CSV fidelity notes + omissions expander. */
    .ob-strong-info {
      margin-top: -0.25rem;
    }
    .ob-strong-note {
      margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      max-width: 65ch;
    }
    .ob-omissions {
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-omissions summary {
      cursor: pointer;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-omissions-list {
      margin: 0.5rem 0;
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
    }
    .ob-omissions-list li {
      margin: 0.15rem 0;
    }

    .ob-preview {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
    .ob-session-card {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-session-card h3 {
      margin: 0;
    }
    .ob-session-date {
      margin: 0.15rem 0 0.75rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }
    .ob-session-parts {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-preview-more {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      font-style: italic;
    }

    /* Hevy body-measurement preview: one small Type / Value table per day. */
    .ob-meas-table {
      width: 100%;
      margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
    }
    .ob-meas-table td {
      padding: 0.3rem 0.5rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
    }
    .ob-meas-table tr:first-child td {
      border-top: none;
    }
    .ob-meas-type {
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-meas-value {
      text-align: right;
      font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
      white-space: nowrap;
      color: var(--sl-color-text);
    }
    .ob-meas-tag {
      font-family: var(--sl-font-mono);
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      padding: 0.05rem 0.35rem;
      border-radius: 0.25rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }
    .ob-exercise-list {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.6rem;
    }
    .ob-exercise-name {
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 0 0 0.2rem;
    }
    .ob-set-list {
      margin: 0;
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }

    /* Bodyweight EWMA trend chart (two-series line: faint raw dots + bold trend). */
    .ob-trend {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-trend .ob-summary-subhead {
      margin-top: 0;
    }
    .ob-line-wrap {
      max-width: 48rem;
    }
    .ob-line {
      display: block;
      max-width: 100%;
      height: auto;
    }
    .ob-line-trend {
      fill: none;
      stroke: var(--sl-color-accent);
      stroke-width: 2;
      stroke-linejoin: round;
      stroke-linecap: round;
    }
    .ob-line-raw {
      fill: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      opacity: 0.5;
    }
    .ob-line-end {
      fill: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }
    .ob-line-end.is-latest {
      fill: var(--sl-color-accent);
    }
    .ob-line-guide {
      stroke: var(--sl-color-hairline);
      stroke-width: 1;
      stroke-dasharray: 2 3;
    }
    .ob-line-label {
      fill: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      font-family: var(--sl-font);
      font-size: 11px;
    }
    .ob-line-label.is-value {
      fill: var(--sl-color-text-accent);
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ob-trend-note {
      margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
      max-width: 65ch;
    }

    /* Compact per-day measurements table, horizontally scrollable so wide metric sets
       (many circumferences) never break the page layout. */
    .ob-tablewrap {
      overflow-x: auto;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
    }
    .ob-meas-grid {
      border-collapse: collapse;
      width: 100%;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      margin: 0;
    }
    .ob-meas-grid th,
    .ob-meas-grid td {
      padding: 0.35rem 0.7rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .ob-meas-grid thead th {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      text-align: right;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
    }
    .ob-meas-grid thead th:first-child,
    .ob-meas-grid .ob-meas-daterow {
      text-align: left;
    }
    .ob-meas-grid tbody tr:last-child th,
    .ob-meas-grid tbody tr:last-child td {
      border-bottom: none;
    }
    .ob-meas-daterow {
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-meas-grid .ob-meas-value {
      text-align: right;
      font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
      color: var(--sl-color-text);
    }

    /* Collapsed verbose surfaces: per-session breakdown + raw-JSON expander. */
    .ob-preview-stack {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .ob-breakdown > summary,
    .ob-raw > summary {
      cursor: pointer;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-raw {
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
    }
    .ob-raw-json {
      max-height: 24rem;
      overflow: auto;
      margin: 0.6rem 0 0;
      padding: 0.75rem;
      border-radius: 0.4rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg);
      font-family: var(--sl-font-mono);
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
    }

    .ob-btn {
      font: inherit;
      font-weight: 600;
      padding: 0.6rem 1.1rem;
      border-radius: 0.4rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-accent);
      cursor: pointer;
      width: fit-content;
    }
    .ob-btn-primary {
      background-color: var(--sl-color-accent);
      color: var(--sl-color-black);
    }
    .ob-btn-secondary {
      background-color: transparent;
      color: var(--sl-color-text-accent);
    }
    .ob-btn-ghost {
      background-color: transparent;
      border-color: transparent;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      font-weight: 400;
    }

    .ob-email-card {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-email-title {
      margin: 0 0 0.2rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ob-email-sub {
      margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }
    .ob-email-row {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .ob-email-row input[type="email"] {
      flex: 1 1 16rem;
      font: inherit;
      padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;
      border-radius: 0.4rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg);
      color: var(--sl-color-text);
    }
    .ob-email-status {
      margin: 0.6rem 0 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
    }
    .ob-email-status.is-success {
      color: var(--sl-color-text-accent);
    }
    .ob-email-status.is-pending {
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }

    /* ===================================================================================
       PHASE C — convert cockpit. One accent (the site's --sl-color-accent), calibrated
       grays via --sl-color-*, tabular numerals, consistent chart grammar, both themes.
       ================================================================================== */

    /* CVD-validated categorical palette for SOURCE IDENTITY only (never for quantities).
       Base :root carries the dark values (Starlight's base theme is dark); the light
       overrides apply under [data-theme="light"]. */
    :root,
    :root[data-theme="dark"] {
      --ob-src-hevy: #3e8fcb;
      --ob-src-strong: #e3672f;
      --ob-src-apple: #25a67d;
      --ob-src-strava: #b67f14;
      --ob-src-json: #be6e9c;
    }
    :root[data-theme="light"] {
      --ob-src-hevy: #0072b2;
      --ob-src-strong: #d55e00;
      --ob-src-apple: #009e73;
      --ob-src-strava: #e69f00;
      --ob-src-json: #cc79a7;
    }

    .ob-preview :is(h2, h3, h4) { text-wrap: balance; }
    .ob-num, .ob-dtable .num, .ob-tile-value, .ob-cov-tick { font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }

    /* --- coverage hero --- */
    .ob-hero { padding: 0.5rem 0 0; }
    .ob-hero-eyebrow {
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      font-family: var(--sl-font-mono);
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      letter-spacing: 0.09em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--sl-color-text-accent);
    }
    .ob-hero-headline {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3.3vw, 2.1rem);
      font-weight: 600;
      line-height: 1.2;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
      max-width: 26ch;
    }
    .ob-hero-headline .ob-hl { color: var(--sl-color-white); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
    .ob-hero-sub { margin: 0.85rem 0 0; font-size: var(--sl-text-sm); color: var(--sl-color-gray-3); }

    .ob-cov { margin: 1.25rem 0 0; }
    .ob-cov-lanes { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 5px; }
    .ob-cov-lane {
      position: relative;
      height: 14px;
      border-radius: 5px;
      background: var(--sl-color-gray-6);
    }
    .ob-cov-seg { position: absolute; top: 0; bottom: 0; border-radius: 5px; transition: opacity 0.2s ease; }
    .ob-cov-lane.is-off .ob-cov-seg { opacity: 0.18; filter: grayscale(1); }
    .ob-cov-axis {
      position: relative;
      height: 1.1rem;
      margin-top: 6px;
      font-family: var(--sl-font-mono);
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }
    .ob-cov-tick { position: absolute; transform: translateX(-50%); white-space: nowrap; }
    .ob-cov-tick:first-child { transform: none; }

    /* --- merge receipt strip --- */
    .ob-merge-strip {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 6px 10px;
      padding: 0.65rem 0.95rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-ms-item b { color: var(--sl-color-white); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
    .ob-ms-item b.ob-ms-accent { color: var(--sl-color-text-accent); }
    .ob-ms-dot { color: var(--sl-color-gray-4); }
    .ob-ms-kept { color: var(--sl-color-text-accent); font-weight: 600; }
    .ob-ms-how { flex-basis: 100%; margin-top: 2px; }
    .ob-ms-how summary { cursor: pointer; color: var(--sl-color-gray-3); font-size: var(--sl-text-xs); width: max-content; }
    .ob-ms-how p { margin: 0.5rem 0 0; max-width: 72ch; font-size: var(--sl-text-sm); color: var(--sl-color-gray-2); }

    /* --- source chips --- */
    .ob-sources-head { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
    .ob-sources-h {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }
    .ob-sources-hint { margin: 0.15rem 0 0; font-size: var(--sl-text-sm); color: var(--sl-color-gray-3); }
    .ob-chips-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; }
    .ob-chip2 {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 999px;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .ob-chip2.is-off { opacity: 0.55; }
    .ob-chip2-toggle {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      font: inherit;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-text);
      background: transparent;
      border: 0;
      padding: 0.4rem 0.5rem 0.4rem 0.75rem;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
    .ob-chip2:not(.is-off) { border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-accent) 45%, var(--sl-color-hairline)); }
    .ob-chip2-dot { width: 9px; height: 9px; border-radius: 50%; flex: none; }
    .ob-chip2.is-off .ob-chip2-dot { filter: grayscale(1); }
    .ob-chip2-n { color: var(--sl-color-gray-3); font-size: var(--sl-text-xs); }
    .ob-chip2-remove {
      font: inherit;
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      background: transparent;
      border: 0;
      border-left: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      padding: 0.4rem 0.6rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      align-self: stretch;
    }
    .ob-chip2-remove:hover { color: #b3261e; }

    /* --- stat tiles --- */
    .ob-tiles { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(11rem, 1fr)); gap: 0.75rem; }
    .ob-tile {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.15rem;
      padding: 0.85rem 0.95rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-tile-label {
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ob-tile-value {
      font-size: 1.65rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      line-height: 1.1;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      color: var(--sl-color-white);
      font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    }
    .ob-tile-unit { font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--sl-color-gray-3); margin-left: 3px; }
    .ob-tile-chip { margin-top: 2px; font-family: var(--sl-font-mono); font-size: var(--sl-text-xs); color: var(--sl-color-gray-2); }

    /* --- cards (shared) --- */
    .ob-card {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.6rem;
      padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-card-head { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    .ob-card-h { margin: 0; font-size: var(--sl-text-lg); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--sl-color-white); }
    .ob-card-sub { margin: 0.25rem 0 0; font-size: var(--sl-text-sm); color: var(--sl-color-gray-3); max-width: 66ch; }
    .ob-head-row { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .ob-chart { width: 100%; }
    .ob-chart .ob-line, .ob-chart .ob-spark { display: block; max-width: 100%; height: auto; }

    .ob-takeaway {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      align-items: baseline;
      margin: 0.85rem 0 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-base);
      color: var(--sl-color-text);
    }
    .ob-takeaway b { font-weight: 600; }
    .ob-take-ico { color: var(--sl-color-text-accent); font-weight: 700; flex: none; }
    .ob-caveat {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.45rem;
      align-items: baseline;
      margin: 0.6rem 0 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      max-width: 76ch;
    }
    .ob-caveat-ico { color: var(--sl-color-gray-4); flex: none; }

    /* SVG chart additions: phase bands, PR rings. */
    .ob-line-band { fill: var(--sl-color-gray-4); opacity: 0.13; }
    .ob-line-band-label {
      fill: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      font-family: var(--sl-font-mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      dominant-baseline: middle;
    }
    .ob-line-pr { fill: var(--sl-color-bg-nav); stroke: var(--sl-color-accent); stroke-width: 2; }

    /* --- insight card (accent-tinted) --- */
    .ob-insight { border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-accent) 35%, var(--sl-color-hairline)); }
    .ob-insight-take {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.55rem;
      align-items: baseline;
      margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-lg);
      color: var(--sl-color-text);
    }
    .ob-insight-take b { font-weight: 600; color: var(--sl-color-white); }
    .ob-insight-ico { color: var(--sl-color-text-accent); flex: none; }

    /* --- data tables inside cards --- */
    .ob-dtable { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: var(--sl-text-sm); min-width: 460px; }
    .ob-dtable th, .ob-dtable td { text-align: left; padding: 0.4rem 0.7rem; }
    .ob-dtable thead th {
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      font-weight: 600;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
    }
    .ob-dtable td.num, .ob-dtable th.num { text-align: right; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
    .ob-dtable tbody tr + tr td, .ob-dtable tbody tr + tr th { border-top: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline); }
    .ob-dtable .ob-spark { height: 30px; }
    .ob-tag { font-family: var(--sl-font-mono); font-size: var(--sl-text-xs); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; font-weight: 600; }
    .ob-tag-new { color: var(--sl-color-text-accent); }
    .ob-tag-forgot { color: #b3791a; }
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .ob-tag-forgot, :root:not([data-theme="light"]) .ob-tag-forgot { color: #d69f4a; }

    /* --- lift switcher --- */
    .ob-lift-switch {
      display: inline-flex;
      gap: 2px;
      padding: 3px;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg);
    }
    .ob-lift-switch button {
      font: inherit;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
      background: transparent;
      border: 0;
      padding: 0.3rem 0.7rem;
      border-radius: 0.35rem;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
    .ob-lift-switch button[aria-selected="true"] {
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
      color: var(--sl-color-white);
      font-weight: 600;
      box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    }

    /* --- volume small-multiples --- */
    .ob-volrows { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
    .ob-volrow {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 6rem 1fr auto;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.9rem;
      padding: 0.5rem 0;
    }
    .ob-volrow + .ob-volrow { border-top: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline); }
    .ob-vol-label { font-size: var(--sl-text-sm); font-weight: 500; }
    .ob-vol-spark .ob-spark { height: 32px; }
    .ob-vol-meta { font-family: var(--sl-font-mono); font-size: var(--sl-text-xs); color: var(--sl-color-gray-2); text-align: right; white-space: nowrap; }
    .ob-vol-flag { color: var(--sl-color-gray-3); }

    .ob-conf { margin: 0.6rem 0 0; font-size: var(--sl-text-sm); color: var(--sl-color-gray-2); }
    .ob-conf-chip {
      display: inline-block;
      font-family: var(--sl-font-mono);
      font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      padding: 0.1rem 0.45rem;
      border-radius: 0.3rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }
    .ob-disc-list { margin: 0.75rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; font-size: var(--sl-text-sm); color: var(--sl-color-gray-2); }
    .ob-disc-list li { margin: 0.15rem 0; }
    .ob-disc-list b { color: var(--sl-color-text); }

    /* --- collapsed details & raw --- */
    .ob-details { border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline); border-radius: 0.6rem; background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav); }
    .ob-details > summary { cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; color: var(--sl-color-gray-2); padding: 0.85rem 1.1rem; }
    .ob-details-body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 0 1.1rem 1.1rem; }
    .ob-details-h {
      margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      padding-bottom: 0.35rem;
    }

    /* --- three-tier import notes --- */
    .ob-notes { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; }
    .ob-notes-h { margin: 0 0 0.15rem; font-size: var(--sl-text-lg); font-weight: 600; color: var(--sl-color-white); }
    .ob-note {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.7rem;
      align-items: flex-start;
      padding: 0.65rem 0.8rem;
      border-radius: 0.45rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .ob-note-ico { flex: none; font-weight: 700; }
    .ob-note-body { color: var(--sl-color-gray-2); }
    .ob-note-body b { color: var(--sl-color-text); }
    .ob-note-good { background-color: color-mix(in srgb, #2e955f 12%, transparent); }
    .ob-note-good .ob-note-ico { color: #2e955f; }
    .ob-note-info { background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-gray-4) 12%, transparent); }
    .ob-note-info .ob-note-ico { color: var(--sl-color-gray-3); }
    .ob-note-warn { background-color: color-mix(in srgb, #b3791a 15%, transparent); }
    .ob-note-warn .ob-note-ico { color: #b3791a; }
    :root:not([data-theme="light"]) .ob-note-good .ob-note-ico { color: #4fbb84; }
    :root:not([data-theme="light"]) .ob-note-warn .ob-note-ico { color: #d69f4a; }

    /* --- export bar --- */
    .ob-export {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
      gap: 1.25rem;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 1.25rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.6rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-export-h { margin: 0; font-size: var(--sl-text-lg); font-weight: 600; color: var(--sl-color-white); }
    .ob-export-copy p { margin: 0.5rem 0 0; font-size: var(--sl-text-sm); color: var(--sl-color-gray-2); max-width: 58ch; }
    .ob-export-copy .ob-export-advocacy { color: var(--sl-color-gray-3); font-size: var(--sl-text-xs); margin-top: 0.5rem; }
    .ob-export-actions { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: stretch; min-width: 15rem; }
    .ob-export-actions .ob-btn { width: 100%; text-align: center; }
    .ob-export-note { font-family: var(--sl-font-mono); font-size: var(--sl-text-xs); color: var(--sl-color-gray-3); text-align: center; }

    .ob-cockpit-empty { margin: 0; font-size: var(--sl-text-base); color: var(--sl-color-gray-2); }

    @media (max-width: 40rem) {
      .ob-export { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .ob-export-actions { min-width: 0; }
      .ob-volrow { grid-template-columns: 5rem 1fr; grid-template-rows: auto auto; }
      .ob-vol-meta { grid-column: 2; text-align: left; }
    }
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      .ob-cov-seg { transition: none; }
    }
  </style>
</StarlightPage>
